{
  "format": 1,
  "name": "Vibe Phaser",
  "isInstrument": false,
  "explanation": "A photocell vibe and phaser: a four-stage all-pass network is swept by a slow, asymmetric optical LFO (a lamp seen through a light-dependent resistor — fast warm-up, slow cool-down) so the notches glide unevenly for a watery, throbbing movement. Switch between Chorus (phase-shifted path blended with the dry signal) and Vibrato (100% wet pitch wobble), and shape it with Rate, Depth, Intensity and Mix.",
  "params": [
    {
      "name": "Rate",
      "index": 0,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.32
    },
    {
      "name": "Depth",
      "index": 1,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.7
    },
    {
      "name": "Mode",
      "index": 2,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0
    },
    {
      "name": "Intensity",
      "index": 3,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.6
    },
    {
      "name": "Mix",
      "index": 4,
      "min": 0,
      "max": 1,
      "default": 0.5
    }
  ],
  "wasmBase64": "",
  "html": "<!doctype html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\">\n<style>\n/* ============================================================\n   VIBE PHASER — a photocell Uni-Vibe.\n   Throbbing lamp + light-dependent resistor behind a frosted\n   dome, watery purple swirl, walnut + cream 1960s organ chassis.\n   ============================================================ */\n@property --lamp{syntax:'<number>';inherits:true;initial-value:0}\n\n:root{\n  --ac:#9b8cff;            /* photocell glow */\n  --ac2:#c0a0ff;           /* lamp hot core */\n  --cream:#e9e2d0;\n  --walnut1:#3a2a22;\n  --walnut2:#241712;\n  --plate:#cfc6b2;\n}\n*{box-sizing:border-box}\nhtml,body{height:100%}\nbody{\n  margin:0;\n  font:13px ui-sans-serif,Georgia,system-ui,-apple-system,serif;\n  color:#2a211b;\n  background:\n    radial-gradient(120% 90% at 50% -10%,#241a14 0%,#160d09 60%,#0a0604 100%);\n  display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;\n  padding:18px;\n  -webkit-font-smoothing:antialiased;\n}\n\n/* ---------- the chassis: a walnut organ-effect box ---------- */\n.chassis{\n  position:relative;\n  width:100%;max-width:600px;\n  border-radius:14px;\n  padding:0;\n  overflow:hidden;\n  background:\n    repeating-linear-gradient(96deg,rgba(0,0,0,.16) 0 2px,transparent 2px 7px),\n    linear-gradient(150deg,#4a352a 0%,var(--walnut1) 40%,var(--walnut2) 100%);\n  border:1px solid #1a100a;\n  box-shadow:\n    0 36px 80px rgba(0,0,0,.7),\n    inset 0 2px 0 rgba(255,225,190,.14),\n    inset 0 -3px 14px rgba(0,0,0,.6);\n}\n/* brushed metal faceplate */\n.face{\n  position:relative;\n  margin:13px;\n  border-radius:8px;\n  padding:18px 20px 22px;\n  background:\n    linear-gradient(180deg,#d9d0bc,#bcb19a 55%,#a89c83 100%);\n  box-shadow:\n    inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.6),\n    inset 0 -2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.32),\n    0 3px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.45);\n}\n.face::after{ /* fine engraving grain */\n  content:\"\";position:absolute;inset:0;border-radius:8px;pointer-events:none;\n  background:repeating-linear-gradient(90deg,rgba(255,255,255,.05) 0 1px,transparent 1px 3px);\n  mix-blend-mode:overlay;opacity:.5;\n}\n\n/* ---------- header / nameplate ---------- */\n.head{position:relative;z-index:3;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:13px;margin-bottom:14px}\n.screw{width:11px;height:11px;border-radius:50%;\n  background:radial-gradient(circle at 35% 30%,#fff,#9a8f78 60%,#5d5340);\n  box-shadow:inset 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,.6),0 1px 1px rgba(255,255,255,.4)}\n.screw::before{content:\"\";position:absolute;width:11px;height:2px;background:rgba(0,0,0,.45);\n  transform:rotate(40deg) translateY(4.5px);border-radius:2px}\n.title{flex:1}\n.title h1{\n  margin:0;font-family:Georgia,\"Times New Roman\",serif;font-weight:800;\n  font-size:23px;letter-spacing:.02em;color:#2b1d15;line-height:1;\n  text-shadow:0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.45);\n}\n.title .sub{margin-top:3px;font-size:9.5px;letter-spacing:.42em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#6a5a44}\n.plate-stamp{\n  font-family:Georgia,serif;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;\n  color:#5a4c39;border:1px solid #8d7f64;border-radius:3px;padding:4px 8px;background:rgba(0,0,0,.06);\n}\n\n/* ---------- main stage: lamp on left, controls on right ---------- */\n.stage{position:relative;z-index:2;display:grid;grid-template-columns:166px 1fr;gap:18px;align-items:center}\n\n/* ====== THE THROBBING LAMP + PHOTOCELL DOME ====== */\n.lampwell{\n  --lamp:0;\n  position:relative;width:166px;height:198px;border-radius:12px;\n  background:\n    radial-gradient(circle at 50% 38%,#1c1320 0%,#0d0712 60%,#070409 100%);\n  border:2px solid #15100c;\n  box-shadow:inset 0 0 30px rgba(0,0,0,.9),inset 0 2px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.06),0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.5);\n  overflow:hidden;\n  cursor:ns-resize;touch-action:none;user-select:none;\n}\n/* watery purple swirl — two slow counter-rotating conic washes */\n.swirl,.swirl2{position:absolute;inset:-30%;border-radius:50%;mix-blend-mode:screen;\n  opacity:calc(.25 + var(--lamp)*.6)}\n.swirl{\n  background:conic-gradient(from 0deg,\n    transparent 0deg,color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) 70%,transparent) 60deg,\n    transparent 130deg,color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac2) 60%,transparent) 220deg,transparent 300deg);\n  filter:blur(14px);\n  animation:swirlA calc(9s / (.5 + var(--lamp))) linear infinite;\n}\n.swirl2{\n  background:conic-gradient(from 180deg,\n    transparent 0deg,color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac2) 55%,transparent) 80deg,\n    transparent 160deg,color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) 65%,transparent) 250deg,transparent 330deg);\n  filter:blur(20px);\n  animation:swirlB calc(13s / (.5 + var(--lamp))) linear infinite reverse;\n}\n@keyframes swirlA{to{transform:rotate(360deg)}}\n@keyframes swirlB{to{transform:rotate(360deg)}}\n\n/* the lamp glass dome */\n.dome{position:absolute;left:50%;top:50%;width:96px;height:96px;transform:translate(-50%,-54%);\n  border-radius:50%;\n  background:\n    radial-gradient(circle at 50% 38%,\n      color-mix(in srgb,#fff calc(var(--lamp)*70%),var(--ac2)) 0%,\n      color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac2) calc(40% + var(--lamp)*55%),#1a1024) 22%,\n      color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) calc(20% + var(--lamp)*40%),#120a1c) 48%,\n      rgba(20,12,30,.2) 74%, transparent 80%);\n  box-shadow:\n    0 0 calc(14px + var(--lamp)*60px) calc(2px + var(--lamp)*22px) color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) 80%,transparent),\n    inset 0 -6px 16px rgba(0,0,0,.5);\n  /* the optical \"warm-up fast, cool-down slow\" throb baked as fallback;\n     JS overrides --lamp live from Rate/Depth, but standalone it still breathes */\n  animation:throb 3.6s cubic-bezier(.12,.85,.2,1) infinite;\n}\n@keyframes throb{\n  0%{--lamp:.05}\n  14%{--lamp:1}      /* fast warm-up */\n  100%{--lamp:.05}   /* slow cool-down */\n}\n/* filament cross seen inside the bulb */\n.dome::before{content:\"\";position:absolute;left:50%;top:36%;width:30px;height:30px;\n  transform:translate(-50%,-50%);\n  background:\n    linear-gradient(transparent 46%,color-mix(in srgb,#fff calc(var(--lamp)*100%),var(--ac2)) 46% 54%,transparent 54%),\n    linear-gradient(90deg,transparent 46%,color-mix(in srgb,#fff calc(var(--lamp)*100%),var(--ac2)) 46% 54%,transparent 54%);\n  opacity:calc(.4 + var(--lamp)*.6);filter:blur(.4px)}\n/* frosted glass highlight */\n.dome::after{content:\"\";position:absolute;left:24%;top:18%;width:34px;height:22px;border-radius:50%;\n  background:radial-gradient(circle,rgba(255,255,255,.6),transparent 70%);filter:blur(2px);opacity:.7}\n\n/* the photocell (LDR) — a little squiggle-eyed sensor staring at the lamp */\n.ldr{position:absolute;left:50%;bottom:16px;transform:translateX(-50%);\n  width:46px;height:22px;border-radius:11px;\n  background:linear-gradient(#3a3128,#1c1610);\n  border:1px solid #0c0805;box-shadow:inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.12),0 1px 3px rgba(0,0,0,.6)}\n.ldr::before{content:\"\";position:absolute;inset:4px;border-radius:7px;\n  background:\n    repeating-linear-gradient(60deg,#d9b14a 0 2px,#1c1610 2px 4px);\n  opacity:calc(.35 + var(--lamp)*.65);\n  box-shadow:0 0 calc(2px + var(--lamp)*10px) color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac2) 70%,transparent)}\n\n/* lamp label */\n.lamp-lbl{position:absolute;left:0;right:0;top:9px;text-align:center;z-index:4;\n  font-size:8.5px;letter-spacing:.36em;text-transform:uppercase;\n  color:color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac2) calc(40% + var(--lamp)*60%),#5a4c66);\n  text-shadow:0 0 calc(var(--lamp)*10px) var(--ac)}\n.lamp-rate{position:absolute;left:0;right:0;bottom:42px;text-align:center;z-index:4;\n  font:700 12px ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace;color:#e9e2d0;\n  text-shadow:0 0 8px color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) calc(var(--lamp)*100%),transparent)}\n\n/* ---------- controls column ---------- */\n.controls{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:14px}\n.knobrow{display:flex;gap:10px;justify-content:space-between}\n\n/* a cream chickenhead-style organ knob */\n.ctl{position:relative;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:6px;flex:1}\n.knob{position:relative;width:70px;height:70px;cursor:ns-resize;touch-action:none;user-select:none}\n.skirt{position:absolute;inset:0;border-radius:50%;\n  background:radial-gradient(circle at 50% 32%,#fbf6ea,#cdc3ab 62%,#9b9079 100%);\n  box-shadow:0 3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.4),inset 0 -3px 6px rgba(0,0,0,.22),inset 0 2px 2px rgba(255,255,255,.7)}\n/* ring of value glow under the cap */\n.glowring{position:absolute;inset:-4px;border-radius:50%;\n  background:conic-gradient(from 225deg,\n    color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) 90%,transparent) calc(var(--n,0)*270deg),\n    rgba(0,0,0,.18) calc(var(--n,0)*270deg) 270deg, transparent 270deg);\n  filter:drop-shadow(0 0 calc(3px + var(--n,0)*8px) color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) 70%,transparent));\n  -webkit-mask:radial-gradient(circle,transparent 33px,#000 34px);\n  mask:radial-gradient(circle,transparent 33px,#000 34px);\n  transition:--n .12s ease}\n/* the chickenhead pointer */\n.beak{position:absolute;left:50%;top:50%;width:30px;height:11px;margin:-5.5px 0 0 -3px;\n  transform-origin:3px 50%;\n  transform:rotate(calc((var(--n,0) - .5) * 270deg - 90deg));\n  transition:transform .12s cubic-bezier(.2,.75,.25,1)}\n.beak::before{content:\"\";position:absolute;inset:0;border-radius:3px 8px 8px 3px;\n  background:linear-gradient(#403228,#1d150f);\n  box-shadow:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.5),inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.18);\n  clip-path:polygon(0 18%,62% 0,100% 50%,62% 100%,0 82%)}\n.hub{position:absolute;left:50%;top:50%;width:13px;height:13px;margin:-6.5px 0 0 -6.5px;border-radius:50%;\n  background:radial-gradient(circle at 40% 35%,#5a4738,#180f0a);box-shadow:inset 0 0 2px rgba(0,0,0,.7)}\n.bub{position:absolute;top:-12px;left:50%;transform:translate(-50%,4px) scale(.7);opacity:0;pointer-events:none;\n  font:700 11px ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace;color:#160d09;background:var(--ac2);padding:2px 7px;border-radius:5px;\n  box-shadow:0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,.4);transition:.14s;white-space:nowrap;z-index:5}\n.knob.act .bub,.ctl:hover .bub{opacity:1;transform:translate(-50%,0) scale(1)}\n\n.nm{font:700 9.5px ui-sans-serif,system-ui;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#4a3c2c;text-align:center}\n.val{font:700 12px ui-monospace,Menlo,monospace;color:#2b1d15}\n\n/* ---------- the MODE rocker (Chorus / Vibrato) ---------- */\n.rocker{position:relative;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;gap:6px}\n.toggle{position:relative;width:150px;height:42px;border-radius:9px;cursor:pointer;user-select:none;\n  background:linear-gradient(#1c130d,#0c0805);\n  border:1px solid #0a0604;\n  box-shadow:inset 0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,.8),inset 0 -1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.06)}\n.tlabels{position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;z-index:1;pointer-events:none}\n.tlabels span{flex:1;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;\n  font:700 10px ui-sans-serif,system-ui;letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#7d6f57;transition:.18s}\n.toggle[data-on=\"0\"] .tlabels span:first-child,\n.toggle[data-on=\"1\"] .tlabels span:last-child{color:#fdf6e6;text-shadow:0 0 8px var(--ac2)}\n.slug{position:absolute;top:3px;left:3px;width:72px;height:36px;border-radius:7px;z-index:0;\n  background:linear-gradient(180deg,#e9e2d0,#bdb29a);\n  box-shadow:0 2px 5px rgba(0,0,0,.5),inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255,255,255,.8),inset 0 -2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,.18),\n    0 0 14px color-mix(in srgb,var(--ac) 45%,transparent);\n  transition:transform .26s cubic-bezier(.5,1.6,.4,1)}\n.toggle[data-on=\"1\"] .slug{transform:translateX(72px)}\n\n.footnote{position:relative;z-index:2;margin-top:16px;padding-top:11px;border-top:1px solid rgba(0,0,0,.2);\n  font:11px Georgia,serif;font-style:italic;line-height:1.5;color:#5b4c39}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"chassis\">\n  <div class=\"face\">\n    <div class=\"head\">\n      <span class=\"screw\"></span>\n      <div class=\"title\">\n        <h1>Vibe Phaser</h1>\n        <div class=\"sub\">Photocell Vibe &middot; Phaser</div>\n      </div>\n      <span class=\"plate-stamp\">Optical&nbsp;LFO</span>\n      <span class=\"screw\"></span>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"stage\">\n      <!-- THE LAMP : drag it to set Rate; its throb shows the optical LFO -->\n      <div class=\"lampwell\" id=\"lampwell\" data-i=\"0\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"1\" data-def=\"0.32\" data-step=\"0.001\">\n        <div class=\"swirl\"></div>\n        <div class=\"swirl2\"></div>\n        <div class=\"lamp-lbl\">Optical LFO</div>\n        <div class=\"dome\" id=\"dome\"></div>\n        <div class=\"ldr\"></div>\n        <div class=\"lamp-rate\" id=\"lamprate\">0.32</div>\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"controls\">\n        <div class=\"knobrow\">\n          <div class=\"ctl\" data-i=\"1\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"1\" data-def=\"0.7\" data-step=\"0.001\">\n            <div class=\"knob\">\n              <i class=\"skirt\"></i><i class=\"glowring\"></i><i class=\"beak\"></i><i class=\"hub\"></i>\n              <span class=\"bub\"></span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"nm\">Depth</div><div class=\"val\"></div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"ctl\" data-i=\"3\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"1\" data-def=\"0.6\" data-step=\"0.001\">\n            <div class=\"knob\">\n              <i class=\"skirt\"></i><i class=\"glowring\"></i><i class=\"beak\"></i><i class=\"hub\"></i>\n              <span class=\"bub\"></span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"nm\">Intensity</div><div class=\"val\"></div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"ctl\" data-i=\"4\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"1\" data-def=\"0.5\" data-step=\"0.001\">\n            <div class=\"knob\">\n              <i class=\"skirt\"></i><i class=\"glowring\"></i><i class=\"beak\"></i><i class=\"hub\"></i>\n              <span class=\"bub\"></span>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"nm\">Mix</div><div class=\"val\"></div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"rocker\">\n          <div class=\"toggle\" id=\"mode\" data-on=\"0\" data-i=\"2\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"1\" data-def=\"0\" data-step=\"1\">\n            <div class=\"slug\"></div>\n            <div class=\"tlabels\"><span>Chorus</span><span>Vibrato</span></div>\n          </div>\n          <div class=\"nm\">Mode</div>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"footnote\">A lamp seen through a photocell &mdash; fast warm-up, slow cool-down &mdash; sweeps a four-stage all-pass network for watery, throbbing movement.</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<script>\nfunction boot(){\n  function send(i,v){ if(window.vstai&&window.vstai.setParam) window.vstai.setParam(i,v); }\n  function fmt(v,step){ var d = step>=1?0:(step>=0.1?1:(step>=0.01?2:3)); return (+v).toFixed(d); }\n\n  // live \"optical lamp\" state, driven by Rate + Depth, animated on rAF.\n  var rate=0.32, depth=0.7, lampPhase=0, lastT=0;\n  var dome=document.getElementById('dome');\n  var lampwell=document.getElementById('lampwell');\n  var lamprate=document.getElementById('lamprate');\n\n  function lampLoop(t){\n    if(!lastT) lastT=t;\n    var dt=Math.min(0.05,(t-lastT)/1000); lastT=t;\n    // Rate maps to ~0.15..6 Hz of the optical LFO\n    var hz = 0.15 + rate*rate*5.85;\n    lampPhase += dt*hz;\n    if(lampPhase>1) lampPhase-=Math.floor(lampPhase);\n    // asymmetric optical response: fast warm-up, slow cool-down (skewed triangle)\n    var up=0.18, p=lampPhase, tri = p<up ? p/up : 1-(p-up)/(1-up);\n    var lamp = Math.pow(Math.max(0,tri),0.7) * (0.18 + depth*0.82);\n    // disable the CSS fallback throb once JS is driving it\n    dome.style.animation='none';\n    lampwell.style.setProperty('--lamp', lamp.toFixed(3));\n    requestAnimationFrame(lampLoop);\n  }\n  requestAnimationFrame(lampLoop);\n\n  // ---- the lamp doubles as the RATE control (vertical drag) ----\n  (function(){\n    var c=lampwell, i=+c.dataset.i, mn=+c.dataset.min, mx=+c.dataset.max, def=+c.dataset.def, step=+c.dataset.step||0.001;\n    var val=def;\n    function norm(){ return (val-mn)/(mx-mn||1); }\n    function paint(){ rate=norm(); lamprate.textContent=fmt(val,step); send(i,val); }\n    function setN(n){ n=n<0?0:(n>1?1:n); var v=mn+(mx-mn)*n; v=Math.round(v/step)*step; val=v; paint(); }\n    c.addEventListener('pointerdown',function(e){ c._d=1;c._y=e.clientY;c._n=norm(); c.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId); e.preventDefault(); });\n    c.addEventListener('pointermove',function(e){ if(!c._d)return; setN(c._n+(c._y-e.clientY)/220); });\n    c.addEventListener('pointerup',function(){ c._d=0; });\n    c.addEventListener('pointercancel',function(){ c._d=0; });\n    c.addEventListener('dblclick',function(){ val=def; paint(); });\n    c.addEventListener('wheel',function(e){ e.preventDefault(); setN(norm()+(e.deltaY<0?0.02:-0.02)); },{passive:false});\n    paint();\n  })();\n\n  // ---- the three chickenhead knobs ----\n  function wireKnob(c){\n    var i=+c.dataset.i, mn=+c.dataset.min, mx=+c.dataset.max, def=+c.dataset.def, step=+c.dataset.step||0.001;\n    var val=def, knob=c.querySelector('.knob'), ring=c.querySelector('.glowring'),\n        beak=c.querySelector('.beak'), out=c.querySelector('.val'), bub=c.querySelector('.bub');\n    var isDepth = (i===1);\n    function norm(){ return (val-mn)/(mx-mn||1); }\n    function paint(){\n      var n=norm();\n      ring.style.setProperty('--n',n); beak.style.setProperty('--n',n);\n      var t=fmt(val,step); out.textContent=t; bub.textContent=t;\n      if(isDepth) depth=n;\n      send(i,val);\n    }\n    function setN(n){ n=n<0?0:(n>1?1:n); var v=mn+(mx-mn)*n; v=Math.round(v/step)*step; val=v; paint(); }\n    knob.addEventListener('pointerdown',function(e){ knob._d=1;knob._y=e.clientY;knob._n=norm(); knob.classList.add('act'); knob.setPointerCapture(e.pointerId); e.preventDefault(); });\n    knob.addEventListener('pointermove',function(e){ if(!knob._d)return; setN(knob._n+(knob._y-e.clientY)/200); });\n    knob.addEventListener('pointerup',function(){ knob._d=0; knob.classList.remove('act'); });\n    knob.addEventListener('pointercancel',function(){ knob._d=0; knob.classList.remove('act'); });\n    knob.addEventListener('dblclick',function(){ val=def; paint(); });\n    knob.addEventListener('wheel',function(e){ e.preventDefault(); setN(norm()+(e.deltaY<0?0.02:-0.02)); },{passive:false});\n    paint();\n  }\n  var ctls=document.querySelectorAll('.ctl');\n  for(var j=0;j<ctls.length;j++) wireKnob(ctls[j]);\n\n  // ---- the MODE rocker (Chorus 0 / Vibrato 1) ----\n  (function(){\n    var t=document.getElementById('mode'), i=+t.dataset.i, def=+t.dataset.def;\n    function set(v){ v=v?1:0; t.dataset.on=v; send(i,v); }\n    t.addEventListener('click',function(){ set(t.dataset.on===\"1\"?0:1); });\n    t.addEventListener('dblclick',function(e){ e.stopPropagation(); set(def); });\n    set(def);\n  })();\n}\nif(window.vstai&&window.vstai.onReady) window.vstai.onReady(boot); else boot();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>\n",
  "assembly": "// =====================================================================\n//  VIBE PHASER — photocell vibe / phaser (Uni-Vibe-style modulation)\n//  A 4-stage first-order all-pass phase-shift network swept by a slow,\n//  ASYMMETRIC \"photocell\" LFO (a lamp seen through a light-dependent\n//  resistor: fast warm-up, slow cool-down). Each all-pass stage centres\n//  on a different frequency and is modulated by a slightly staggered,\n//  exponentially-shaped sweep, so the notches glide unevenly — the watery,\n//  throbbing movement of a vintage optical vibe. Two voices:\n//    • CHORUS   — phase-shifted path mixed back with the dry input\n//                 (comb-like notches sweep → shimmering \"vibe\").\n//    • VIBRATO  — 100% wet all-pass output (pure pitch/phase wobble).\n//  Pure algorithm, no samples.\n// =====================================================================\n\nconst MAX_FRAMES: i32 = 8192;\nconst MAX_CHANNELS: i32 = 2;\nconst MAX_PARAMS: i32 = 64;\nconst STAGES: i32 = 4;\n\nconst inBuf:  StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_FRAMES * MAX_CHANNELS);\nconst outBuf: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_FRAMES * MAX_CHANNELS);\nconst params: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_PARAMS);\n\nlet sampleRate: f32 = 48000.0;\nlet channels: i32 = 2;\n\n// all-pass z-1 state per channel per stage  (channel * STAGES + stage)\nconst apState: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_CHANNELS * STAGES);\n// LFO phase per channel (stereo spread keeps the two sides drifting apart)\nconst lfoPhase: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(MAX_CHANNELS);\n\n// Per-stage nominal centre frequencies (Hz). A real vibe staggers its four\n// photocell-driven all-pass cells across the spectrum; these glide together.\nconst stageHz: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(STAGES);\n// Per-stage sweep span (Hz) — deeper stages move more, like the staggered cells.\nconst stageSpan: StaticArray<f32> = new StaticArray<f32>(STAGES);\n\nconst P_RATE: i32 = 0;      // 0..1 -> ~0.05 .. 12 Hz throb\nconst P_DEPTH: i32 = 1;     // 0..1 -> how far the cells sweep\nconst P_MODE: i32 = 2;      // <0.5 chorus, >=0.5 vibrato (100% wet)\nconst P_INTENSITY: i32 = 3; // 0..1 -> how hard the lamp drives (sweep curvature / range)\nconst P_MIX: i32 = 4;       // 0..1 dry/wet (chorus only; vibrato is always 100% wet)\n\nconst TWO_PI: f32 = 6.2831853;\nconst PI: f32 = 3.14159265;\n\nexport function init(sr: f32, maxFrames: i32, numChannels: i32): void {\n  sampleRate = sr > 0.0 ? sr : 48000.0;\n  channels = numChannels < MAX_CHANNELS ? numChannels : MAX_CHANNELS;\n  for (let i = 0; i < MAX_CHANNELS * STAGES; i++) apState[i] = 0.0;\n  // start the two channels a quarter cycle apart for a wide, living image\n  lfoPhase[0] = 0.0;\n  lfoPhase[1] = 0.25;\n\n  // four staggered cells, low → high; spans chosen so notches stay musical\n  stageHz[0] = 220.0;  stageSpan[0] = 180.0;\n  stageHz[1] = 520.0;  stageSpan[1] = 420.0;\n  stageHz[2] = 1150.0; stageSpan[2] = 900.0;\n  stageHz[3] = 2400.0; stageSpan[3] = 1700.0;\n\n  params[P_RATE] = 0.32;\n  params[P_DEPTH] = 0.7;\n  params[P_MODE] = 0.0;\n  params[P_INTENSITY] = 0.6;\n  params[P_MIX] = 0.5;\n}\n\nexport function getInputPtr(): usize  { return changetype<usize>(inBuf); }\nexport function getOutputPtr(): usize { return changetype<usize>(outBuf); }\nexport function getParamsPtr(): usize { return changetype<usize>(params); }\nexport function getNumParams(): i32   { return 5; }\n\n@inline function clampf(x: f32, lo: f32, hi: f32): f32 {\n  return x < lo ? lo : (x > hi ? hi : x);\n}\n\nexport function process(n: i32): void {\n  const rate01: f32 = clampf(params[P_RATE], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const depth01: f32 = clampf(params[P_DEPTH], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const vibrato: bool = params[P_MODE] >= 0.5;\n  const intensity: f32 = clampf(params[P_INTENSITY], 0.0, 1.0);\n  const mix01: f32 = clampf(params[P_MIX], 0.0, 1.0);\n\n  // Rate: exponential 0.05 .. ~12 Hz so the knob feels musical end-to-end.\n  const rateHz: f32 = f32(0.05 * Mathf.exp(rate01 * 5.48)); // 0.05 .. ~12 Hz\n  const lfoInc: f32 = rateHz / sampleRate;                  // cycles per sample\n\n  // Intensity widens the sweep range and (via the photocell shaping below)\n  // bends the optical curve so the throb gets harder and more asymmetric.\n  const sweep: f32 = depth01 * (0.45 + 0.55 * intensity); // 0..1 fraction of each span\n\n  // Wet level trim: 4 cascaded all-passes are unity-gain, but the chorus\n  // sum (dry+wet) can reach ~2× at the comb peaks — trim so peak stays <1.\n  const wetTrim: f32 = vibrato ? 1.0 : 0.5;\n  const dryTrim: f32 = vibrato ? 0.0 : 0.5;\n  // small safety so blended peaks never exceed ~1.0\n  const outGain: f32 = 0.96;\n\n  for (let c = 0; c < channels; c++) {\n    const base: i32 = c * MAX_FRAMES;\n    const sbase: i32 = c * STAGES;\n    let phase: f32 = lfoPhase[c];\n\n    for (let f = 0; f < n; f++) {\n      // --- photocell LFO -------------------------------------------------\n      // Start from a sine, then bias it through an exponential transfer so\n      // the rise is faster than the fall (lamp heats quick, cools slow):\n      // an asymmetric, throbbing 0..1 control voltage.\n      const s: f32 = f32(Mathf.sin(phase * TWO_PI)); // -1..1\n      const u: f32 = 0.5 + 0.5 * s;                   // 0..1 raw\n      // optical shaping: gamma-like curve, asymmetric about the midpoint\n      const shaped: f32 = f32(Mathf.pow(u, 1.0 + intensity * 1.4));\n      // blend raw + shaped so low intensity stays near a clean sweep\n      const cv: f32 = (1.0 - intensity * 0.6) * u + (intensity * 0.6) * shaped;\n\n      // advance LFO\n      phase += lfoInc;\n      if (phase >= 1.0) phase -= 1.0;\n\n      const x: f32 = inBuf[base + f];\n\n      // --- 4-stage all-pass cascade, each cell swept by the photocell ----\n      let y: f32 = x;\n      for (let st = 0; st < STAGES; st++) {\n        // staggered modulation: deeper stages lag a touch via curve shaping\n        const m: f32 = sweep * cv;                 // 0..1 sweep position\n        let fc: f32 = stageHz[st] + stageSpan[st] * m * (0.6 + 0.4 * f32(st) / 3.0);\n        // keep coefficient stable & below Nyquist\n        const nyq: f32 = sampleRate * 0.45;\n        if (fc > nyq) fc = nyq;\n        if (fc < 20.0) fc = 20.0;\n        // first-order all-pass coefficient from tan of the warped corner\n        const t: f32 = f32(Mathf.tan(PI * fc / sampleRate));\n        let a: f32 = (t - 1.0) / (t + 1.0);\n        if (a > 0.999) a = 0.999;\n        if (a < -0.999) a = -0.999;\n        const z: f32 = apState[sbase + st];\n        const ap: f32 = a * y + z;          // all-pass output\n        apState[sbase + st] = y - a * ap;   // update state\n        y = ap;\n      }\n\n      let wet: f32;\n      let outv: f32;\n      if (vibrato) {\n        // VIBRATO: 100% wet — pure swept all-pass (phase/pitch wobble).\n        wet = y;\n        outv = wet * wetTrim;\n      } else {\n        // CHORUS: blend dry + phase-shifted path; the sweeping notches give\n        // the shimmering optical \"vibe\". Mix scales the wet contribution.\n        wet = x * dryTrim + y * wetTrim;\n        outv = x * (1.0 - mix01) + wet * mix01;\n      }\n\n      outBuf[base + f] = clampf(outv * outGain, -1.0, 1.0);\n    }\n\n    lfoPhase[c] = phase;\n  }\n}\n",
  "publishedAt": 1751000034000
}